MzF8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Benjamin Davies"},"description":"The capital and largest city of the United Kingdom, home to iconic landmarks including Big Ben, Tower Bridge, and Buckingham Palace. Millions visit annually for its world-class museums, theatres, shopping, and rich history spanning nearly 2,000 years."},{"rank":2,"name":"Edinburgh","placeId":"edinburgh","regionId":"scotland_lowlands","regionName":"Scottish Lowlands","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1506377585622-bedcbb027afc?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxFZGluYnVyZ2glMjBDYXN0bGUlMjBjaXR5c2NhcGUlMjBzdW5zZXR8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4MzMyNTM0Nnww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Adam Wilson"},"description":"Scotland's stunning capital city dominated by Edinburgh Castle perched on an extinct volcanic rock, featuring the historic Royal Mile connecting the castle to the Palace of Holyroodhouse. The city seamlessly blends medieval architecture with Georgian elegance, offering world-class museums, galleries, theaters, and vibrant cultural festivals throughout the year."},{"rank":3,"name":"Manchester","placeId":"manchester","regionId":"england_north_west","regionName":"North West England","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1724135869739-6055627ba5df?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxNYW5jaGVzdGVyJTIwY2l0eSUyMHNreWxpbmV8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4MzMyMjE2MHww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Mylo Kaye"},"description":"England's second-largest city, Manchester is a vibrant cultural and industrial hub with world-class museums, galleries, and a legendary music scene. It's home to impressive Victorian architecture, cutting-edge contemporary art, and excellent restaurants and nightlife."},{"rank":4,"name":"Bath","placeId":"bath","regionId":"england_south_east","regionName":"South East England","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1594755652327-b8514471741b?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxCYXRoJTIwUm95YWwlMjBDcmVzY2VudCUyMEdlb3JnaWFufGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODMzMjIwNzF8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Liv Cashman"},"description":"A UNESCO World Heritage city famous for its exquisite Georgian architecture built from honey-coloured stone, centred around the Roman Baths and Bath Abbey. The Royal Crescent and Circus are architectural masterpieces, while the city offers excellent museums, restaurants, and riverside walks along the Avon."},{"rank":5,"name":"Stratford-upon-Avon","placeId":"stratford_upon_avon","regionId":"england_west_midlands","regionName":"West Midlands","image":null,"description":"The birthplace of William Shakespeare, this charming market town on the Avon is one of England's most visited destinations with Tudor architecture and literary heritage. Shakespeare's Birthplace and the Royal Shakespeare Theatre are must-sees."},{"rank":6,"name":"Windsor","placeId":"windsor","regionId":"england_south_east","regionName":"South East England","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1667743989159-5f0a38d46c2e?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxXaW5kc29yJTIwQ2FzdGxlJTIwVGhhbWVzfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODMzMjIwNjV8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Tadas Petrokas"},"description":"A charming riverside town crowned by Windsor Castle, the iconic royal residence sprawling majestically above the Thames. Visitors enjoy boat trips on the river, exploring the castle's State Rooms and Chapel, and strolling the picturesque Georgian High Street."},{"rank":7,"name":"Snowdonia National Park","placeId":"snowdonia_national_park","regionId":"wales_north","regionName":"North Wales","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1486576123198-d6afd2782a0a?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxTbm93ZG9uaWElMjBtb3VudGFpbnMlMjBXYWxlc3xlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzMzMwMjA2fDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Mitchell Orr"},"description":"Wales's largest national park featuring Snowdon, the highest peak in Wales, surrounded by dramatic mountains, glacial lakes, and ancient forests. It's essential for hiking, mountaineering, scenic drives, and immersing yourself in pristine Welsh wilderness."},{"rank":8,"name":"York","placeId":"york","regionId":"england_yorkshire","regionName":"Yorkshire","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1678889166899-bbbc06682b5e?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxZb3JrJTIwTWluc3RlciUyMGNhdGhlZHJhbHxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzMzI1MzExfDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Al Elmes"},"description":"A walled medieval city with a stunning Gothic cathedral (York Minster) and well-preserved city walls offering panoramic views. The charming Shambles street and riverside walks make it one of England's most atmospheric historic destinations."},{"rank":9,"name":"Lake District National Park","placeId":"lake_district_national_park","regionId":"england_north_west","regionName":"North West England","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1609264799042-4530f0321797?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxMYWtlJTIwRGlzdHJpY3QlMjBOYXRpb25hbCUyMFBhcmslMjBVbml0ZWQlMjBLaW5nZG9tfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODQwMjIwOTJ8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Glen Farrelly"},"description":"England's most celebrated national park featuring picturesque lakes, mountains, and valleys that inspired Romantic poets like Wordsworth. Outdoor enthusiasts visit for hiking, water sports, scenic drives, and charming fell-foot villages nestled among stunning natural landscapes."},{"rank":10,"name":"Stonehenge","placeId":"stonehenge","regionId":"england_south_west","regionName":"South West England","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1599833975787-5c143f373c30?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxTdG9uZWhlbmdlJTIwc3RhbmRpbmclMjBzdG9uZXMlMjBtb251bWVudHxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzMzIyMTA0fDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"K. Mitch Hodge"},"description":"An enigmatic prehistoric monument of standing stones on Salisbury Plain, dating back over 5,000 years and representing one of the world's most mysterious archaeological wonders. Its scale, precision, and purpose continue to captivate millions of visitors annually."}]}